# Assignment 3: Network Topologies using Cisco Packet Tracer

## Objective
To create different network topologies and verify connectivity using the ping command.

---

## Q1: Connect one PC with another PC

PC1 -------- PC2  

Result: Ping successful between both PCs.

---

## Q2: Connect a PC with Router

PC -------- Router  

Result: PC successfully communicates with router.

---

## Q3: Connect 2 PCs

PC1 -------- PC2  

Result: Communication successful.

---

## Q4: Connect 2 PCs using Switch

PC1 -------- Switch -------- PC2  

Result: Communication successful through switch.

---

## Q5: Bus Topology

PC1 --- PC2 --- PC3 --- PC4  

Result: All PCs connected in bus topology and ping successful.

---

## Q6: Ring Topology

PC1 --- PC2 --- PC3 --- PC4 --- PC1  

Result: Circular communication established successfully.

---

## Q7: Extended Ring Topology

PC1 --- PC2 --- PC3 --- PC4 --- PC5 --- PC1  

Result: Extended ring created and communication verified.

---

## Q8: Tree Topology

            Switch  
           /      \  
        PC1       PC2  
       /            \  
     PC3            PC4  

Result: Hierarchical topology created and all nodes connected successfully.

---

## Conclusion

Different network topologies such as point-to-point, bus, ring, and tree were created successfully and connectivity was verified using ping command.
